# Autotask Swagger UI Integration

## Base URL Structure
- Format: `[API URL]/atservicesrest/v1.0/`
- Region-specific API URLs must be used for authentication
- All API description: autotask rest api, must append endpoints to the base URL
- Example: `[API URL]/atservicesrest/v1.0/ActionTypes`

## Authentication Headers
Required headers for all API description: autotask rest api,:
- `ApiIntegrationCode`: Your integration code
- `UserName`: API user account name
- `Secret`: API user password
- `ImpersonationResourceId` (optional): Resource ID for impersonation actions

## Regional Endpoints
Key production endpoints:
```plaintext
Australia/NZ: https://webservices6.autotask.net/atservicesrest
EU1 (Europe/Asia): https://webservices19.autotask.net/atservicesrest
UK: https://webservices4.autotask.net/atservicesrest
America East: https://webservices3.autotask.net/atservicesrest
```

## Request Methods
Supported HTTP methods:
- GET: Retrieve data
- POST: Create new resources
- PUT: Update existing resources
- PATCH: Partial updates
- DELETE: Remove resources

## Response Handling
- Responses return in JSON format
- Downloadable response files available for data extraction
- Error responses include standard HTTP status codes
- Response structure follows Swagger specification format

## Implementation Notes
1. Use platform-specific URLs for authentication
2. Cannot authenticate across non-native zones
3. Entity operations require appropriate permissions
4. Impersonation only works on supported entities/actions
5. Query models define required request structures

## Technical Limitations
- Authentication restricted to assigned zone
- API calls must follow platform threading limits
- Impersonation limited to specific entity types
- Response pagination may be required for large datasets
